title: Amherst tops final readers' poll
text:
Amherst tops final readers' poll Robert Mentzer , Gannett Wisconsin Media 12:54 p.m. CDT October 13, 2015 Buy Photo Amherst's Mitchell Glodowski, center, celebrates his touchdown in the first quarter with his teammates during the Central Wisconsin Conference football game against Pacelli at Goerke Field in Stevens Point on Friday, Sept. 18, 2015. (Photo: Megan McCormick/Stevens Point Journal Media) Buy Photo CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Our sports reporters each week make their power rankings for central Wisconsin prep football teams. And each week throughout the regular season, we asked readers to cast their votes for the top teams in the region. These will be our last reader rankings of the season. 
Here in descending order are readers' Central Wisconsin Prep Sports Power Rankings: 
10. Port Edwards 
Congrats to local teams on a great season! See you in the playoffs. Buy Photo Marathon beat Edgar, 16-8, at Edgar, Friday, October 2, 2015.
